products, jellies, condensation protein, gelatin gel, bread, etc. The current 
study is the first to comprehend various tea protein extraction methods and 
their amino acid profile. The preparation of tea protein bioactive peptides and 
hydrolysates are summarized. Several functional properties (solubility, foaming 
capacity, emulsification, water/oil absorption capacity) and bioactivities 
(antioxidant, antihypertensive, antidiabetic) of tea proteins are emphasized.

